<h2>
    FAQs About Salmon Fishing Near Bend
</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Can I catch salmon directly from Bend?</strong><br>
        No, but kokanee are plentiful in nearby lakes; Chinook requires traveling to the Lower Deschutes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>When is kokanee season?</strong><br>
        June through September—trolling and jigging produce peak results.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>What’s the best area for Chinook?</strong><br>
        Below Sherar’s Falls on the Lower Deschutes from August to October
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Need a guide from Bend?</strong><br>
        Local services are available and include equipment, instruction, and permit help.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Can Coho salmon be caught here?</strong><br>
        Yes, but they are incidental on Chinook trips around September–October
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Which gear works best?</strong><br>
        Use medium-heavy spinning rods, braid/fluoro setups, flashers, spoons, roe rigs, and spinnerbaits.
    </li>
</ol>
